From: STGR Browser Team <dev@stgr-browser.dev>
Date: Tue, 6 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: Auto-hide for vertical tabs sidebar

Implements auto-hide behavior for the vertical tabs sidebar:
- Collapses to a thin 12px vertical strip when not in use (VSCode-style)
- Expands on hover over the strip with a 100ms delay
- Collapses on mouse leave with an 800ms delay (cancellable on re-entry)
- Pin button in the bottom bar to keep the sidebar expanded
- Clicking outside the sidebar when auto-hide is active collapses it
- Smooth CSS transitions for width, opacity, and box-shadow
- Vertical gradient accent bar visible in collapsed state
- Pref observer for live toggling of auto-hide
- Proper lifecycle cleanup in destroy()

